    "answer": "The Protoss Robotics Facility can train 5 units. Here are their costs (minerals/gas), supply, build time, and prerequisites:\n\n| Unit | Minerals | Gas | Supply | Build Time | Prerequisite |\n|------|----------|-----|--------|------------|--------------|\n| **WarpPrism** | 250 | 0 | 2 | 50 s | Robotics Facility (no extra building) |\n| **Observer** | 25 | 75 | 1 | 25 s | Robotics Facility |\n| **Immortal** | 250 | 100 | 4 | 55 s | Robotics Facility |\n| **Colossus** | 300 | 200 | 6 | 75 s | Robotics Facility + **Robotics Bay** |\n| **Disruptor** | 150 | 150 | 4 | 50 s | Robotics Facility + **Robotics Bay** |\n\n- All units share the base tech path: **Pylon → Gateway → Cybernetics Core → Robotics Facility**.\n- **Colossus** and **Disruptor** additionally require a **Robotics Bay** attached to the Robotics Facility.\n- **WarpPrism** and **Observer** have no extra building requirement.\n- **Time** is listed in seconds (converted from game frames; normal speed assumed, but exact in-game seconds may vary with game speed settings)."
